  <prompt>
    Build `ClauseAnalyzerHandler` — an LLM-assisted `IToolHandler` implementation per
    FR-14 that performs contract clause structuring with structural diff. Pipeline:
    input clause text → LLM structured-output call → produces typed clause representation
    (e.g., `{ type: "indemnification", parties: [...], scope: "...", carveOuts: [...],
    monetaryCap: "...", terminationConditions: [...] }`) → optional structural diff
    against a reference template if provided.

    Configurable via `sprk_analysistool.sprk_configuration`: `clauseTypes` (allow-list
    of recognized types — e.g., Indemnification, LimitationOfLiability, Confidentiality,
    Termination, Assignment, GoverningLaw, ForceMajeure); `referenceTemplate` (optional
    template clause to diff against); `modelDeployment` override.

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100 — implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "ClauseAnalyzerHandler"`; lives in
    `Services/Ai/Handlers/ClauseAnalyzerHandler.cs`. Requires `sprk_analysistool` row
    with `sprk_handlerclass = "ClauseAnalyzerHandler"`.

    LLM call uses existing structured-outputs pattern; respects per-tenant cache (ADR-014)
    + `ai-context` rate limit (ADR-016) + safety pipeline (NFR-13).

    Distinct from `ClauseComparisonHandler` (task 103, deterministic) which DIFFS two
    clauses. This handler STRUCTURES a single clause + optionally diffs against a
    reference template.

    Tests use mocked `IOpenAiClient`. Cover: contract test + positive (each supported
    clauseType structures correctly per mocked LLM response) + error (clauseType not in
    allow-list, LLM returns invalid JSON) + config-driven (clauseTypes subset filters
    output) + cache test.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + Azure OpenAI structured-outputs + legal-domain
    schema experience. Familiar with `IOpenAiClient` patterns + per-tenant cache key
    discipline + the existing safety pipeline contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ClauseAnalyzerHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`; auto-discovered;
    `sprk_analysistool` row deployed with `sprk_handlerclass = "ClauseAnalyzerHandler"`;
    unit tests cover positive + error + config-driven + cache cases; LLM call uses
    existing structured-outputs pattern + respects cache (ADR-014) + rate limit (ADR-016)
    + safety pipeline (NFR-13); BFF publish-size delta ≤+0.6 MB; `code-review` +
    `adr-check` green.
  </goal>

