  <context>
    <background>
      `ClauseAnalyzerHandler` STRUCTURES a single clause — the input is unstructured
      contract text, the output is a typed schema describing the clause. Combined with
      `ClauseComparisonHandler` (task 103), this enables full contract-review workflows:
      analyzer structures each clause, comparison diffs against precedent/template.

      Distinct intent from `ClauseComparisonHandler` (deterministic) — this handler
      requires LLM to UNDERSTAND the clause; deterministic diff cannot do that.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/ClauseAnalyzerHandler.cs (NEW)</file>
