  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. If &gt;70%, run `context-handoff` then `/compact`. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: New LLM-assisted handler; ADR-013/014/016 + NFR-13 binding; FR-14
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: all 11 steps below including Step 9.5 quality gates
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX; confirm 106 is 🔲; dependency 104 (last Wave 1 task) complete.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every &lt;inputs&gt; + &lt;knowledge&gt; file. Extract LLM structured-output
      pattern from `GenericAnalysisHandler.cs`.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Handler Surface + Output Schema">
      Define `HandlerId = "ClauseAnalyzerHandler"`; output schema for typed clause
      representation per type (Indemnification, LimitationOfLiability, etc.); `ConfigSchema`
      with `clauseTypes`, `referenceTemplate`, `modelDeployment`. Inject `IOpenAiClient`,
      cache, `IScopeResolverService`.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Handler">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/ClauseAnalyzerHandler.cs`.
      Pattern: validate input → check per-tenant cache → on miss, call LLM via structured
      outputs with type-specific schema → validate result → if `referenceTemplate`
      provided, compute structural diff between structured clause + template → emit
      `ToolResult`. Telemetry per ADR-015 (no clause text in logs).
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Create `ClauseAnalyzerHandlerTests.cs` using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture`. Mock
      `IOpenAiClient`. Cover: contract; positive (each supported clauseType); error
      (clauseType not allow-listed, LLM invalid JSON); config-driven (clauseTypes
      subset); cache (second identical call hits cache); telemetry (no clause text in
      logs).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Seed sprk_analysistool Row">
      Create `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-clause-analyzer-row.json` with
      `sprk_handlerclass = "ClauseAnalyzerHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "CLAUSE-ANALYZE@v1"`,
      sample `sprk_configuration`, `AvailableInContexts = "Both"`. Deploy to Spaarke
      Dev. Capture evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Tests + Vuln Check">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test --filter "ClauseAnalyzerHandler"`. Run vuln check.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      `dotnet publish -c Release ...`. Report absolute + diff. Target ≤+0.6 MB.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through criteria; record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` + `adr-check`. Both MUST pass. Confirm ADR-013/014/015/016 + NFR-13.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update status `complete`; TASK-INDEX 106 🔲 → ✅; reset `current-task.md`.
    </step>
  </steps>

